1. Modifier
Think of it like a “UI toolkit” you attach to a component.
Used to decorate (background, border), layout (padding, size), or interact (click, scroll).

2. Arrangement (Row / Column)
Controls how children are placed in a Row or Column.
Examples:
Arrangement.Start → items at the start
Arrangement.SpaceBetween → space between items
Arrangement.Center → all in center

3. Alignment
Controls where items sit inside a container (Row, Column, Box).
Examples:
Alignment.CenterHorizontally
Alignment.BottomEnd

4. Size
fillMaxSize() → fills available space
fillMaxWidth() → fills full width
wrapContentSize() → fits content
weight() → distribute space proportionally

5. Styling
background(Color.Red) → set background
border(2.dp, Color.Black) → add border
clip(RoundedCornerShape(12.dp)) → round corners
Combine for Card-like effects.


